summary: This line chart has an x axis representing Year and a y axis representing Youth unemployment rate, with a total of 11 data points.
Overall Youth unemployment rate has increased over the Year

This line chart has an x axis representing Year and a y axis representing Youth unemployment rate, with a total of 11 data points. The chart has 5 significant trends.
The longest trend is moderately constant which exists from 2016 to 2019.
On the contrary, the next significant trend is extremely increasing which exists from 2014 to 2016.
Similarly, the next significant trend is extremely increasing which exists from 2011 to 2013.
Also, the next significant trend is slightly decreasing which exists from 2009 to 2011.
Differently, the next significant trend is moderately constant which exists from 2013 to 2014.
